  <summary date="2017-05-02T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Family-Based Care Services Act of 2017

This bill&#160;establishes a definition, under Medicaid, for&#160;"qualified therapeutic family care services." Specifically, such services are those provided&#160;for children&#160;younger than age 21 who&#160;need institution-level care but can instead be cared for in a community placement through a&#160;licensed and accredited program that: (1) provides children with&#160;certain structured daily activities, and (2) provides parents and caregivers with specialized training and consultation.</summary>
